Arthur James PLACE v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5228. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 12, 1955. No appearance for appellant. William C. Farmer, U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and HUXMAN, Circuit Judge. _

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed, on motion of appellee for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
